{
  "id": "019cdcdc-fd01-7d11-b0d7-a79aa99c1d4d",
  "content": "## Demo: `corvia-workspace` Repository (D50, D51, D52)\n\n### Triple Role\n\n| Role | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| **Template** | `corvia workspace create --template corvia-workspace` scaffolds new workspaces |\n| **Demo** | Clone + open in Codespaces/DevPod → instant working Corvia with real multi-repo knowledge |\n| **Dev environment** | The workspace we use to develop Corvia M3+. Knowledge accumulates as we build. |\n\n\n### Repository Structure\n\n```\ncorvia-workspace/\n├── corvia.toml                      ← [workspace] declaring corvia + adapter\n├── .corvia/                         ← pre-ingested knowledge (checked in)\n│   ├── .git/                        ← knowledge git history\n│   ├── knowledge/                   ← JSON entries for both repos\n│   └── hnsw_index/                  ← pre-built vector index\n├── repos/                           ← .gitignore'd (cloned on init)\n│   └── .gitkeep\n├── .devcontainer/\n│   ├── devcontainer.json\n│   ├── Dockerfile                   ← Corvia binary + Ollama\n│   └── scripts/\n│       ├── post-create.sh           ← clone repos, pull Ollama model\n│       └── post-start.sh            ← corvia serve --mcp &\n├── .gitignore                       ← repos/, .corvia/coordination.redb, ephemeral files\n└── README.md                        ← \"Open in Codespaces\" badge, quickstart\n```\n",
  "source_version": "docs/rfcs/2026-03-01-m2.1-workspace-devcontainer-design.md",
